Hi! I got back from the combat designers; 

So mechanism wise, "**造成伤害" / "the amount of DMG dealt**" is not influenced by how much of said DMG is blocked;

If Goliath deals 391 DMG as it shows in this screenshot, and you have 400 points of Shield, all of it is blocked, and you lose 391 Shield instead of 391 HP. 
But it's still considered that** he dealt 391 DMG**. The amount of DMG dealt is 391 instead of 0, because he did cause you to lose that much Shield (or HP).

We have another type of description that goes " inflict Bleed equal to the amount of **Unblocked DMG**". 

In that case, if he dealt 391 DMG, and your Shield blocked it all, you would not get any Bleed stacks.
